		{
			dependencies: ["55F93CCB1D9F7BDB"]
			description: [
				"[gap=3]"
				"I assume you have already upgraded your &bModel Data&r and started getting &2mob-specific&r &bpredictions&r, so it’s time"
				"[gap=0]"
				"to collect the ACTUAL &eloot&r."
				""
				"Place down this machine, power it with &cFE&r, insert a &bPrediction&r select the desired item on the left and wait"
				"[gap=0]"
				"a few seconds."
				"Once it’s done, take the item from the right side."
				"[gap=3]"
			]
			id: "0EAEB395BFF5ED6F"
			shape: "hexagon"
			size: 1.2d
			subtitle: "&8[Click to read]"
			tasks: [{
				id: "17D6E4B02CCF7B2D"
				item: "hostilenetworks:loot_fabricator"
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "I want the loot already!"
			x: 0.0d
			y: 4.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["3A205A0D5E20FC98"]
			description: [
				"[gap=3]"
				"I hope you did everything you've been"
				"[gap=0]"
				"told earlier, crafted a &bModel Framework&r,"
				"[gap=0]"
				"used it on a mob, and uhh.. on top of that"
				"[gap=0]"
				"make &bPrediction&r &bMatrix&r, don't think much"
				"[gap=0]"
				"of it, it's like a fuel for the chamber. "
				"---"
				"[gap=4]"
				"### &eLet's start!&r"
				"[gap=5]"
				"&e1)&r Craft a &bSimulation Chamber&r."
				"[gap=1]"
				"&e1.1)&r Place it down."
				"[gap=1]"
				"&e1.2)&r Power it with &cFE&r energy."
				"[gap=1]"
				"(Powah or Mekanism)"
				""
				"&e2)&r Insert the &bMob’s Data Model&r."
				"[gap=1]"
				"&e2.1)&r Add &bPrediction Matrix&r."
				"[gap=1]"
				"&e2.2)&r Wait for the process to finish."
				"[gap=6]"
				"---"
				"[gap=4]"
				"Items called &b“Prediction”&r will begin to"
				"[gap=0]"
				"generate. You can convert them into"
				"[gap=0]"
				"specific items depending on the"
				"[gap=0]"
				"&2mob&r you've caught."
				"However.. since your &bModel Data&r is"
				"[gap=0]"
				"still low tier, you will only receive"
				"[gap=0]"
				"dimension-based predictions not"
				"[gap=0]"
				"mob-specific ones."
				""
				"&8><You CAN actually get mob-specific predictions, but your tier is really low, you can view chance by pressing U on the Model Data"
				"[gap=5]"
			]
			icon: "hostilenetworks:sim_chamber"
			id: "55F93CCB1D9F7BDB"
			min_width: 220
			shape: "hexagon"
			size: 1.2d
			subtitle: "&8[Click to read]"
			tasks: [
				{
					id: "3A9F4C9F2CAE18E6"
					item: "hostilenetworks:sim_chamber"
					type: "item"
				}
				{
					id: "70B5F7398376935D"
					item: "hostilenetworks:prediction_matrix"
					type: "item"
				}
			]
			title: "Tamagotchi Chamber"
			x: 0.0d
			y: 2.5d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["418241215D292A5D"]
			description: [
				"### &eModel Framework&r"
				"Used to capture mobs into &bData Models&r which later will be used for machines."
				"---"
				"[gap=3]"
				"&eLet's try it out&r"
				"Get &bDeep Learner&r and &bModel Framework&r, find any mob, right click on a mob with &bModel Framework&r and you'll get his &bModel Data&r."
				"Put it into a &bDeep Learner&r, equip it in a curio slot. and kill the mob so you can &elevel up&r the model and use it later on."
				"---"
				"[gap=3]"
				"&eGo to the next page for&r"
				"[gap=0]"
				"&einformation about Deep Learner&r"
				"{@pagebreak}"
				"### &l&bDeep Learner&r"
				"You can put up to &f4&r &bModel Data's&r"
				"[gap=0]"
				"right click with a &bDeep Learner&r to"
				"[gap=0]"
				"view information of your caught mob."
				"[gap=3]"
				"Putting your mouse on the item in the"
				"[gap=0]"
				"inventory while holding shift will show"
				"[gap=0]"
				"some more information about your"
				"[gap=0]"
				"caught mob."
				"[gap=2]"
				"We'll go through all of it so you can understand everything better."
				"---"
				"[gap=3]"
				"&l&eTier&r"
				"Indicates the level of a &bModel Data&r."
				"Higher tiers increase the chance of obtaining mob predictions."
				"&8(Mob predictions are loot)&r"
				"---"
				"[gap=3]"
				"&l&eData Collected | Per Kill&r"
				"Each time you kill a mob while a &bData Learner&r is equipped, the Data gains points."
				"The number of points scales"
				"[gap=0]"
				"depending on the tier of a &bModel Data&r."
				"---"
				"[gap=3]"
				"&l&eSimulation Cost&r"
				"Represents how much FE is required"
				"[gap=0]"
				"to use this &bModel Data&r in machines."
				"[gap=8]"
				"---"
				"[gap=6]"
				"## That's it!"
			]
